==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Orthocarbonic
<hw>Or`tho*car*bon"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Ortho-</ets> + <ets>carbonic</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Designating a complex ether, <chform>C.(OC2H5)4</chform>, which is
obtained as a liquid of a pleasant ethereal odor by means of
chlorpicrin, and is believed to be a derivative of the hypothetical
normal carbonic acid, <chform>C.(OH)4</chform>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Orthocenter</ent>⟦br⟧
